
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location in a Hyperlambda graph. It retrieves nodes using [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, specifically targeting [limit] and [offset] nodes, and adds them to the path specified by [add]. This is useful for dynamically modifying a graph based on input arguments. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location in the graph.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes specified by an expression, in this case, [limit] and [offset] from [.arguments].
 */
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
